AB  - Exclusion from the joy of experiencing music, especially in concert venues, is especially applicable to those with an auditory impairment. Limited investigations have been carried out into how to reduce the exclusion for this community in attending classical orchestra music concerts. Through utilizing computer technology and human machine interfaces (sensors and cameras) to stimulate complementary senses through interpretation, reducing this exclusion is possible. Case studies are presented in which multi-sensory, multi-modal interpretation of the music is suggested as able to give new meaning and understanding for such individuals. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2023 APA, all rights reserved)
